<line>Edgeworth:
<textEffects>(Now then, what else besides a smell can go both in and out of an open, barred window...? The answer... is <span style="color:#E16935">sound</textEffects>! So, no matter how careful the killer was, if the windows were open, the jig would be up. And since the windows in both Defendant Lobby No. 1 and the hallway were open... ...that explains how <textEffects><span class="hidden"><span class="explain" style="text-decoration: underline dotted" title="Gunshot could be heard - Windows were open, so the gunshot could be heard, but where did it originate from?">the sound of a gunshot could be heard</textEffects></span><textEffects> (Gunshot could be heard - Windows were open, so the gunshot could be heard, but where did it originate from?)</textEffects></span> in both locations!)</span>
</line>

